PN,36703
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F367A1782733687
OL,3,CFashion show celebrates disability,
OL,4,Cinclusion and adaptive fashion
OL,6,FEvery garment has been designed
OL,7,Falongside disabled people, with
OL,8,Ffeatures including front pockets for
OL,9,Fwheelchair users, ring-pull zips for
OL,10,Fpeople with reduced dexterity and
OL,11,Fsleeves with poppers to accommodate
OL,12,Fprosthetic limbs and medical equipment.
OL,14,FDescribed as "part performance, part
OL,15,Fsocial commentary", the catwalk aims
OL,16,Fto encourage conversations about who
OL,17,Ffashion is designed for and how the
OL,18,Fbuilt environment can enable or
OL,19,Fexclude disabled people.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G3/6
